condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Operations Manual Schedule 2, Section I, G, 1, (a) | Description: Six (6) months from the Effective Date of theProject, prepare and furnish to the Association for its review and approval, an operations manual which shall set forth detailedimplementation arrangements for the Contingency Emergency Response.

If by eighteen (18) months after the Effective Date, any Eligible CG has not entered into a participation agreement with theRecipient, the Recipient may select an additional county to participate in the Project, using the criteria set forth in Section Vof Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement and in the PIM.

The Recipient shall establish, by no later than July 31, 2017, a NPSC, to be co-chaired by the Cabinet Secretary of the Recipient’sMoALF and the Chair of Agricultural Committee in the CoG, comprising Permanent Secretaries of the relevant line ministries, two (2)County Governors, Coordinator of the ISAS, and representatives of the private sector and civil society.

The Recipient shall establish, by no later than six (6) months after Effective Date, a management information system database withglobal positioning system coordinates for tracking micro-projects, satisfactory to the Association.

The Recipient shall, by no later than July 31, 2017, establish a NTAC, to be chaired by the Director of Agriculture of theRecipient’s MoALF, comprising directors of relevant line ministry departments, director generals of the relevant governmentagencies, Chair of the ÏTWG responsible for projects/programs, Chair and Secretary of CECAC, and representatives of the privatesector.

The Recipient shall, by no later than July 31, 2017, establish, and maintain thereafter, a NPCU responsible for day-to-dayimplementation of Part D (i) of the Project, comprising NPC, Project Accountant, and internal auditor; procurement, M&E, educationand communication/public relation, ICT, and E&S safeguards compliance officers; and three (3) component coordinators.

The Recipient shall, by no later than four (4) months after Effective Date, designate a Project accountant for the NPCU andassistant accountants for each of the CPCUs under terms of reference and with qualifications satisfactory to the Association.

The Recipient shall, by no later than four (4) months after the Effective Date, establish and maintain in each Eligible County, aCPSC to be chaired by the CEC member for the Agricultural Sector, comprising Chief Officers of the relevant county ministries, aCounty director of environment from NEMA, and representatives from the private sector, civil society, and VMGs.

The Recipient shall, by no later than four (4) months after the Effective Date, establish within an Agricultural Sector departmentin each Eligible County, and maintain CPCU responsible for day-to-day implementation of Parts A, B, C and D (ii) of the Project,comprising CPC, three (3) County Component Leaders, Internal Auditor; County M&E, Accountant, and Procurement Assistants.

The Recipient shall, no later than four (4) months after Effective Date, designate project internal auditors at NPCU and each CPCUunder terms of reference and with qualifications satisfactory to the Association.
